01:43.581 --> 01:44.539
SARAH:
The high school, clinic,

01:44.582 --> 01:46.497
priorities one and two.

01:46.541 --> 01:48.325
Tyler, have you spoken
to Principal Asadi?

01:48.369 --> 01:49.848
He shouldn't be
speaking to anyone.

01:49.892 --> 01:53.678
Maya chose him as her proxy
while she's in L.A., Liz.

01:53.722 --> 01:54.723
Get over it.

01:54.766 --> 01:55.811
Oh, so that's just
how that works?

01:55.854 --> 01:56.986
Fernsby, get over it.Get over it.

01:57.029 --> 01:59.162
Seriously.Get over it!

01:59.206 --> 02:01.991
Seriously.The high school is still wet.

02:02.034 --> 02:03.906
The principal's working out
deals to hold classes

02:03.949 --> 02:05.386
in other places
until it dries out.

02:05.429 --> 02:06.778
What about the clinic?LIZ:
Still wet.

02:06.822 --> 02:08.432
As is all the equipment inside.

02:08.476 --> 02:11.740
The heart monitors, X-ray
machine, MRI, all of it gone.

02:11.783 --> 02:13.785
That sounds like
an expensive problem.

02:13.829 --> 02:15.526
SARAH:Yeah, good thing we're
sitting on a very valuable

02:15.570 --> 02:16.832
mineral deposit.

02:16.875 --> 02:18.442
How close are we
to the first batch of coltan

02:18.486 --> 02:19.878
coming out of
the ground?It's happening as we speak.

02:19.922 --> 02:21.532
I'll have a better update
when we meet again tonight.

02:21.576 --> 02:24.144
Okay. We'll hit the gas
on repairs as soon as revenue

02:24.187 --> 02:25.667
starts flowing.
In the meantime,

02:25.710 --> 02:26.885
we need to stay focused
on getting

02:26.929 --> 02:29.018
official recognition
from the U.S.

02:29.061 --> 02:31.803
Even wealthy countries rely on
their allies in times of crisis.

02:31.847 --> 02:33.675
We have to be able
to do the same

02:33.718 --> 02:35.981
if we're gonna
survive long-term.

